Lawmakers in Tanzania have been banned by Speaker Job Ndugai from entering parliament with fake nails and eye lashes. Ndugai told me he had imposed the ban after Deputy Health Minister Faustine Ndugulile had raised concerns about the health risks posed by fake nails and eye lashes. The ban would also apply to visitors to parliament, he said. Lawmakers are also prohibited from wearing short dresses and jeans to parliament, Ndugai said. Click here for the latest political news 